he Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":61,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Periam was born in 1488, in Exeter, Devon, England, his father, John William Periam, was 19 and his mother, Anne Earl, was 19. He married Grace Blackaller on 1 May 1509, in Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1549, in his hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1488–1549":"1488–1549","1490–1553":"1490–1553","1505–Female":"1505–Surnud","1510–1573":"1510–1573","1515–1573":"1515–1573","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1470–1530":"1470–1530","23 November 1510":"23. november 1510","23 November 1515":"23. november 1515","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1 May 1509":"1. mai 1509","1488":"1488","1510":"1510","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1573":"1573","about 1530":"umbes 1530","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England","Exeter, Devonshire, England":"Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exeter, Exeter district, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Plymouth Dock, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1488–1549"